    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-02T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-02T09:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/305: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-02T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 2, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 2—6:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>133. Your 71, March 27, 9 p.m. Saw <persName corresp="#p_LMM1"
                        >Litvinov</persName> this afternoon. He stated that he would confer with
                        <persName>Rosengoltz</persName> and give me written reply. He attempted to
                    assume that “vague” assurances would suffice. I insisted that you would expect a
                    definite commitment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
